            "language": "zh-HK"
        },
        {
            "title": "聯儲會官員Bostic稱應按兵不動 因通膨依然高企",
            "description": "<div class=\"atoms\"><p class=\"mb-module-gap break-words leading-[1.4] text-px20 lg:text-px18 lg:leading-[1.8] text-batcave\"><span class=\"news-dateline\">【彭博】--</span> 亞特蘭大聯邦儲備銀行行長Raphael Bostic表示，高企的通膨意味著<a class=\"link\" data-i13n=\"sec:content-canvas;subsec:anchor_text;elm:context_link\" data-ylk=\"slk:聯儲會;sec:content-canvas;subsec:anchor_text;elm:context_link;itc:0\" href=\"https://hk.finance.yahoo.com/tag/聯儲會\">聯儲會</a>應該先按兵不動，之後再考慮是否再度降息。</p><p class=\"mb-module-gap break-words leading-[1.4] text-px20 lg:text-px18 lg:leading-[1.8] text-batcave\">Bostic周五在CNBC節目中表示：「我們應該再等等，更有耐心。目前的通膨率仍然過高，所以我認為我們需要在一定程度上具有限制性。」</p><p class=\"mb-module-gap break-words leading-[1.4] text-px20 lg:text-px18 lg:leading-[1.8] text-batcave\">聯儲會官員本周維持基準利率不變。聯儲會主席傑羅姆·鮑威爾表示，該決定得到了政策制定者的廣泛支持。</p><p class=\"mb-module-gap break-words leading-[1.4] text-px20 lg:text-px18 lg:leading-[1.8] text-batcave\">Bostic說：「我感覺比起一個月前，就業市場出現災難性事件這種下行風險如今離我們遠得多。這讓我相信我們可以保持耐心。」</p><div class=\"bg-toast-background -mx-5 -mt-2 mb-3 pb-3 md:-mx-0 lg:mx-auto lg:w-[300px] lg:pb-0\"><div class=\"text-px14 text-gandalf py-1 text-center leading-5\">廣告</div><div class=\"mx-auto text-center min-w-[300px] min-h-[250px]\" id=\"sda-inbody-e9ce9792-8e1b-3c4b-bbbc-301c529e3e34-1-iframe\"><div class=\"bg-dirty-seagull text-px12 text-dolphin mx-auto hidden items-center justify-center only:flex w-[300px] h-[250px]\">廣告</div></div></div><p class=\"mb-module-gap break-words leading-[1.4] text-px20 lg:text-px18 lg:leading-[1.8] text-batcave\">川普周五早些時候宣布，他打算提名凱文·沃什擔任聯儲會下一屆主席。</p><div class=\"recommendation-contents\"><div class=\"bg-marshmallow mb-2 h-[30px] w-[80px] rounded-lg\"></div><div class=\"no-scrollbar -mx-5 mb-5 flex overflow-hidden overflow-x-auto md:-mx-2 lg:mb-3.5\"><div class=\"bg-marshmallow mr-2 ml-5 h-[92px] w-[calc(85%-28px)] flex-shrink-0 rounded-lg md:ml-2 md:w-[calc(85%-16px)] lg:h-[120px] lg:w-[calc(50%-16px)]\"></div><div class=\"bg-marshmallow mx-2 h-[92px] w-[85%] flex-shrink-0 rounded-lg lg:h-[120px] lg:w-[calc(50%-16px)]\"></div></div></div><p class=\"mb-module-gap break-words leading-[1.4] text-px20 lg:text-px18 lg:leading-[1.8] text-batcave\">「我其實和他接觸不多，」Bostic談到沃什時說，「我聽說他很深思熟慮，是個真正可以溝通的人。」</p><p class=\"mb-module-gap break-words leading-[1.4] text-px20 lg:text-px18 lg:leading-[1.8] text-batcave\">本周的會議是Bostic作為政策制定者參加的最後一次會議。他將於2月底退休。</p><p class=\"mb-module-gap break-words leading-[1.4] text-px20 lg:text-px18 lg:leading-[1.8] text-batcave\">原文標題Fed’s Bostic Says Elevated Inflation Should Keep Rates on Hold</p><p class=\"mb-module-gap break-words leading-[1.4] text-px20 lg:text-px18 lg:leading-[1.8] text-batcave\">More stories like this are available on <a class=\"link\" data-ylk=\"slk:bloomberg.com;elm:context_link;itc:0;sec:content-canvas\" href=\"https://www.bloomberg.com\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\">bloomberg.com</a></p><p class=\"mb-module-gap break-words leading-[1.4] text-px20 lg:text-px18 lg:leading-[1.8] text-batcave\">©2026 Bloomberg L.P.</p></div>",
            "link": "https://hk.news.yahoo.com/%E8%81%AF%E5%84%B2%E6%9C%83%E5%AE%98%E5%93%A1bostic%E7%A8%B1%E6%87%89%E6%8C%89%E5%85%B5%E4%B8%8D%E5%8B%95-%E5%9B%A0%E9%80%9A%E8%86%A8%E4%BE%9D%E7%84%B6%E9%AB%98%E4%BC%81-144358723.html",
            "pub_date": "2026-01-31 00:53:22",
            "source": "yahoo_finance_asia",
            "kind": 1,
            "language": "zh-HK"
        },
        {
            "title": "國會預算談判久拖未決 美國聯邦政府再次面臨停擺危機",
            "description": "<div class=\"atoms\"><figure class=\"mb-module-gap\"><div class=\"mx-auto w-fit\"><img alt=\"Source: Bloomberg\" class=\"rounded-lg\" height=\"639\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s.yimg.com/ny/api/res/1.2/9jMRAsgWrqF6ylfBVJjw6w--/YXBwaWQ9aGlnaGxhbmRlcjt3PTk2MDtoPTYzOQ--/https://media.zenfs.com/en/bloomberg_chinese_traditional_757/244a3e44dc4773c2f19f461ffe0f958b\" width=\"960\"/><figcaption class=\"text-px14 text-dolphin mt-2 wrap-anywhere\" style=\"max-width:960px\">Source: Bloomberg</figcaption></div></figure><p class=\"mb-module-gap break-words leading-[1.4] text-px20 lg:text-px18 lg:leading-[1.8] text-batcave\"><br/></p><p class=\"mb-module-gap break-words leading-[1.4] text-px20 lg:text-px18 lg:leading-[1.8] text-batcave\"><span class=\"news-dateline\">【彭博】--</span> 由於國會兩院不太可能在周五午夜的最後期限前通過支出法案，美國聯邦政府勢將面臨短暫停擺。</p><p class=\"mb-module-gap break-words leading-[1.4] text-px20 lg:text-px18 lg:leading-[1.8] text-batcave\">一名共和黨助理表示，參議院可能在周五某個時候就一項政府撥款協議進行表決。但眾議院議長邁克·約翰遜表示，眾議員預計要到周一才會返回華盛頓，這意味著聯邦政府資金將在眾議院通過法案前出現中斷。</p><figure class=\"mb-module-gap\"><div class=\"mx-auto w-fit\"><img alt=\"美國眾院議長約翰遜表示議員預計要到周一才會返回華盛頓Source: Bloomberg\" class=\"rounded-lg\" height=\"639\" src=\"https://s.yimg.com/ny/api/res/1.2/P2owJpLLlGH._KA5qpMb0g--/YXBwaWQ9aGlnaGxhbmRlcjt3PTk2MDtoPTYzOQ--/https://media.zenfs.com/en/bloomberg_chinese_traditional_757/bfa1a2176f43d09bba723f1a36edea87\" width=\"960\"/><figcaption class=\"text-px14 text-dolphin mt-2 wrap-anywhere\" style=\"max-width:960px\">美國眾院議長約翰遜表示議員預計要到周一才會返回華盛頓Source: Bloomberg</figcaption></div></figure><p class=\"mb-module-gap break-words leading-[1.4] text-px20 lg:text-px18 lg:leading-[1.8] text-batcave\">潛在的政府部分停擺僅影響一些聯邦機構，如果在下周初得到解決，預計不會對政府運作造成廣泛影響。</p><p class=\"mb-module-gap break-words leading-[1.4] text-px20 lg:text-px18 lg:leading-[1.8] text-batcave\">儘管如此，一名政府官員指出，財政部、國土安全部、交通部、衛生與公眾服務部以及勞工部在內的受影響機構仍將啟動正式停擺程序。這位官員表示，如果眾議院在周一早些時候通過撥款立法，相關運作可能當天即可恢復。</p><div class=\"bg-toast-background -mx-5 -mt-2 mb-3 pb-3 md:-mx-0 lg:mx-auto lg:w-[300px] lg:pb-0\"><div class=\"text-px14 text-gandalf py-1 text-center leading-5\">廣告</div><div class=\"mx-auto text-center min-w-[300px] min-h-[250px]\" id=\"sda-inbody-03615ae9-4eff-3e57-8ce5-65de27bec084-1-iframe\"><div class=\"bg-dirty-seagull text-px12 text-dolphin mx-auto hidden items-center justify-center only:flex w-[300px] h-[250px]\">廣告</div></div></div><p class=\"mb-module-gap break-words leading-[1.4] text-px20 lg:text-px18 lg:leading-[1.8] text-batcave\">若在午夜發生停擺，這將是國會在美國總統川普第二任期內第二次未能及時為政府提供資金。上一次支出僵局在持續43天後才得以解決，其間導致數百萬家庭的食品援助中斷、數千個航班被取消，並迫使聯邦雇員一個多月未能領取薪酬。</p><div class=\"recommendation-contents\"><div class=\"bg-marshmallow mb-2 h-[30px] w-[80px] rounded-lg\"></div><div class=\"no-scrollbar -mx-5 mb-5 flex overflow-hidden overflow-x-auto md:-mx-2 lg:mb-3.5\"><div class=\"bg-marshmallow mr-2 ml-5 h-[92px] w-[calc(85%-28px)] flex-shrink-0 rounded-lg md:ml-2 md:w-[calc(85%-16px)] lg:h-[120px] lg:w-[calc(50%-16px)]\"></div><div class=\"bg-marshmallow mx-2 h-[92px] w-[85%] flex-shrink-0 rounded-lg lg:h-[120px] lg:w-[calc(50%-16px)]\"></div></div></div><figure class=\"mb-module-gap\"><div class=\"mx-auto w-fit\"><img alt=\"美國國會大廈攝影：格雷姆·斯隆/ 彭博\" class=\"rounded-lg\" height=\"640\" src=\"https://s.yimg.com/ny/api/res/1.2/W36PzqXF19p.yYi09MwPKQ--/YXBwaWQ9aGlnaGxhbmRlcjt3PTk2MDtoPTY0MA--/https://media.zenfs.com/en/bloomberg_chinese_traditional_757/042a7ae4ddad192ac93059025aff74d2\" width=\"960\"/><figcaption class=\"text-px14 text-dolphin mt-2 wrap-anywhere\" style=\"max-width:960px\">美國國會大廈攝影：格雷姆·斯隆/ 彭博</figcaption></div></figure><p class=\"mb-module-gap break-words leading-[1.4] text-px20 lg:text-px18 lg:leading-[1.8] text-batcave\">原文標題US Government Poised for Short Shutdown as Congress Talks Drag</p><p class=\"mb-module-gap break-words leading-[1.4] text-px20 lg:text-px18 lg:leading-[1.8] text-batcave\">--聯合報導 Gregory Korte.</p><p class=\"mb-module-gap break-words leading-[1.4] text-px20 lg:text-px18 lg:leading-[1.8] text-batcave\">More stories like this are available on <a class=\"link\" data-ylk=\"slk:bloomberg.com;elm:context_link;itc:0;sec:content-canvas\" href=\"https://www.bloomberg.com\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\">bloomberg.com</a></p><p class=\"mb-module-gap break-words leading-[1.4] text-px20 lg:text-px18 lg:leading-[1.8] text-batcave\">©2026 Bloomberg L.P.</p></div>",
            "link": "https://hk.news.yahoo.com/%E5%9C%8B%E6%9C%83%E9%A0%90%E7%AE%97%E8%AB%87%E5%88%A4%E4%B9%85%E6%8B%96%E6%9C%AA%E6%B1%BA-%E7%BE%8E%E5%9C%8B%E8%81%AF%E9%82%A6%E6%94%BF%E5%BA%9C%E5%86%8D%E6%AC%A1%E9%9D%A2%E8%87%A8%E5%81%9C%E6%93%BA%E5%8D%B1%E6%A9%9F-164431967.html",
            "pub_date": "2026-01-31 01:48:55",
